description.$t: Lavan is a very smart dog that wants to please who ever he is with. Needs someone who is active and willing to work with him. He has some of the basics sit, down.. He can't be with cat's, livestock and only gets along with female dogs. He currently spends his time with Ella and they have become great friends. He is very loving and just needs a home to come into at night when it's cold and a fenced yard to play in. Lavan is a very smart energetic dog that could be trained for agility work.

Andre is a 1 year old Chihuahua mix. This boy loves attention! He likes to be with his people often and enjoys cuddling. Andre is excellent with other dogs and people! He will steal your heart before you know it! 

Andre's adoption fee is $150 and includes his neuter, all vaccinations (including rabies) and a microchip

Dude spent the early years of his life living in a small home with 60+ other small dogs.  None of them received the attention or love that they so desperately wanted or deserved.  Because of that, Dude is slow to warm up to strangers.  He has already made great strides and is discovering toys for the first time in his young life.  He loves to run around and get treats from your hand. Weighing less than ten pounds, Dude has the personality of a dog several times his sizehe has a terrier attitude and once he learns to trust you, you will see him blossom in front of your eyes.  Dude is good with other dogs and is already neutered and up to date on all of his shots.

Dude is in OAKLEY, UTAH!

If you are interested in adopting Dude, please fill out our application form online. Contact us at info@jasonheiglfoundation.org

Chance is an easy going big lug pit bull mix with a calm and gentle demeanor. His favorite past times are going for walks and taking naps in the sun. Although Chance is a little timid with new people, he warms up quickly, and once he has bonded with a human, he is affectionate and loyal.
 
Chance is estimated to be about 8 years old, already neutered, and up to date on his vaccines. Although he seems to do well with some female dogs, he would prefer to be the only dog in the household, and he does not tolerate cats. Chance really loves to be with his humans more than anything. Therefore, Chance would be best in a home where he isnt left alone for long periods of time.
 
Chance is located in Oakley, Utah.

If you are interested in adopting Chance, please fill out our application form online. Contact us at info@jasonheiglfoundation.org

Roscoe is a 4 1/2 year-old, male Labrador mix. He is a big guy with lots of energy and a love of the outdoors. Roscoe is a very affectionate and happy guy he will even do a dance for you when its time to eat! He needs an active home with no other pets and an experienced owner who is willing to give him the time, attention, and training that he needs. He is a very special dog, and he deserves a very special home! He has been patiently waiting for his forever family for over a year and half now. Come meet and adopt Roscoe today!

Tuffy is an energetic and handsome 7 1/2-year-old red heeler! He is super smart and eager to please. He knows all his basic obedience commands and is fully house trained and crate trained. He loves playing outdoors, and fetching a tennis ball or going for long adventurous hikes. Tuffy needs to be an only pet - he wants and deserves all the attention for himself! He will make a wonderful active companion!

Kevin is an adorable 6 year old male Cocker Spaniel mix. Kevin is a very playful and fun dog. He enjoys leisurely walks, exploring the outdoors and spending time with his favorite humans. He enjoys the company of other friendly dogs and with proper introduction could learn to share a home with a furry feline. Kevin knows some basic obedience commands but a refresher course wouldn't hurt. He is smart and eager to please. Kevin is crate trained and house trained. This great little guy will make a wonderful addition to any family!

Caspian is a handsome and oh so nice Shepherd/Pit Bull mix. He is about a year and a half old and is ready for a family to call his own. He would do great with basic obedience training and lots of activity with his new family. He would make an awesome hiking buddy and will be a constant companion. Make him a part of your family today!

Basil is a sweet 6 year old male Bassett Hound mix. He is a happy go lucky dog! Basil knows a few obedience commands (sit & down) Further obedience training wouldn't hurt. He is very eager to learn and very eager to please. He gets along well with other similar sized dogs but is not too found of the felines. Basil enjoys going to leisurely walks, exploring the outdoors, playing with toys and hanging out with his favorite humans. Basil will make a great companion for any family!
